24/01/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- The commander of the Greek Navy visits Turkey on Monday (24 January) for talks with his Turkish counterpart, Ozden Ornek. This would be the first trip to Turkey by a Greek commander that is not linked to a multilateral conference or event. Vice Admiral Antonios Antoniadis is also due to inspect naval facilities in Istanbul and Golcuk. The visit reflects recent progress in relations between the two countries. (NTV - 24/01/05; AFP - 23/01/05)
